<p>Groups has been moved to it's own mount at /Volumes/Groups which is now set to automount on valid authentication. This move leaves the root partition from being almost completely full to about 430G available space. /Volumes/Babylon will be repurposed to /Volumes/Users with automount enabled for users directories.&nbsp;<br /><br />Groups currently is organized as such:<br /><img src="http://i55.tinypic.com/2cmorbp.png" alt="" width="776" height="452" />&nbsp;</p>
<p>The "workgroup" folder will probably be expired. &nbsp;Network login is now possible even though not currently required.<br />/Volumes/TM will most likely become /Volumes/Public which will be an area that is open to Guests as read only and users in specific read/write with the caveat that anything there is subject to deletion on a complete whim etc.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Certificates have been issued and reassigned for both ISAW local and serv1.isaw.nyu.edu. The previous one had expired October of last year and was never trusted by the server itself for some reason.</p>
<p>Spotlight indexing is now working again with 20 hours remaining on the index process first pass. There is still much to do.</p>